This paper deals with capacity characterization of wireless networks with relays, feedback, cooperation, and full duplex operation. These topics are closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also considers the impact of these factors on the overall system performance, which falls under the category of control and systems engineering (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of physical channels for transmitter/receiver cooperation, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography (cs.CR).
